snippet.textDisplay: Honestly, what the fuck is this shit. I'm sorry but if bad bunny would've handled this collab head on, this song would be a whole lot different and better. It sounds like too much drake, and a little of bad bunny. And the whole point in making songs is that, the sound should be different,  something we've never heard before.  Take karol g  and niki for example.  Tusa is the #1 song played worldwide.  I just think that maybe when this collab was happening,  drake wanted to be the bigger man, and this song doesnt hype up. When bad bunny's verse came up (all late btw) that sound was different from the whole song. Aka, not matching the sound of the beginning.  (Which you extended quite a lot.)  If band bunny's sound was the beginning and Drake's sound in the middle for that small unexpected twist , just like Echame la culpa,  Despasito, taki taki, and s/o. I just think, this song would've sounded better if the 'men' worked together , rather than 'act-alpha'.
